page.title: 15LANDSCAPE
page.content: Three_quarters of the block is rural in character. Here are the rolling hills and valleys of the gently sloping dip of the chalk, North Downs.In places a power station by the River Thames, can be clearly seen.There are thickly wooded hilltops,arable fields crossed by ancient hedges and the relentless pylons march on. Miles of footpaths twist through the woods, meadows and parks, passing silent houses, hidden by fences, trees and bushes. Tiny villages are tucked away in winding lanes in this delightful area. In the western part of the area lies the suburban blot of the 2Oth century, a busy road surrounded by houses.
